WEBVTT

00:00:00.930 --> 00:00:04.155
Friends, welcome to Word on Fire Catholic Ministries.

00:00:04.696 --> 00:00:18.376
Word on Fire is an apostolate dedicated to the mission of evangelization, using media both old and new to share the faith on every continent and to facilitate an encounter with Christ and His Church.

00:00:19.117 --> 00:00:26.688
The efforts of Word on Fire engage the culture and bring the transformative power of God's Word where it is most needed.

00:00:26.708 --> 00:00:27.890
Today,

00:00:27.970 --> 00:00:36.003
We invite you to join Bishop Robert Barron as he preaches the Gospel and shares the warmth and light of Christ with each one of us.

00:00:41.091 --> 00:00:41.732
Peace be with you.

00:00:41.952 --> 00:00:46.760
Friends, we come to this Sunday right before the commencement of the Holy Season of Lent.

00:00:47.321 --> 00:00:51.327
And the church is giving us something of great moment, I think, to reflect upon.

00:00:52.048 --> 00:00:55.794
And it's the centrality of freedom

00:00:56.098 --> 00:01:00.104
and choice for the good at the center of the spiritual life.

00:01:01.747 --> 00:01:04.512
Can I start here with a quote from Thomas Moore?

00:01:04.632 --> 00:01:09.439
It's featured in Man for All Seasons, but I think it's based on something Moore actually wrote.

00:01:09.860 --> 00:01:23.442
He's talking to his daughter, Meg, and he says, God made the plants for their simplicity and the animals for their innocence, but man he made to serve him wittily in the tangle of his mind.

00:01:24.034 --> 00:01:31.022
Moore's reflecting on the variety in creation, that all the different aspects of creation give glory to God in their own particular way.

00:01:31.583 --> 00:01:46.620
But the human being he made with intellect and will and precisely in the tangle of the mind and in the sometimes conflictual quality of the will, he wants us to give him glory.

00:01:47.180 --> 00:01:48.802
Now what am I talking about here more precisely?

00:01:49.363 --> 00:01:52.306
Well look, there are a lot of things in creation that are just, they are

00:01:52.482 --> 00:01:54.105
That way, they're just necessary.

00:01:54.185 --> 00:01:57.050
Think of rocks and quarks and elemental things.

00:01:57.070 --> 00:01:58.272
They're just there.

00:01:58.653 --> 00:02:01.658
God made them for their necessity and simplicity.

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:06.887
But He wants us to give Him glory in a particular way.

00:02:08.009 --> 00:02:09.752
See, we could be marionettes.

00:02:09.772 --> 00:02:16.343
We could just be automatons that act the way God wants us to act because He's making us do it.

00:02:17.084 --> 00:02:18.226
But God doesn't want that.

00:02:18.658 --> 00:02:25.406
He wants us to serve Him wittily in the tangle of our minds, meaning that we come to search out the truth.

00:02:26.507 --> 00:02:30.411
And then He wants us, listen now, to love Him.

00:02:30.471 --> 00:02:38.841
See, an automaton, or a cork or a rock, I mean, they're good, they're fine, but they're not going to love God.

00:02:39.361 --> 00:02:42.105
They can't imitate the love that God is.

00:02:43.186 --> 00:02:46.930
But we, precisely because we have intellect and will,

00:02:47.522 --> 00:02:52.649
are able to respond to God's love with an authentic love of our own.

00:02:54.311 --> 00:02:58.496
If God were just compelling us to act in a particular way, well, we wouldn't be loving Him.

00:02:58.536 --> 00:03:02.201
If God were simply menacing us all the time, we wouldn't be loving Him.

00:03:03.343 --> 00:03:05.826
He wants us to choose.

00:03:08.169 --> 00:03:10.692
Unfree things can't love.

00:03:11.373 --> 00:03:12.655
Only free things can love.

00:03:13.857 --> 00:03:14.898
Now, you know, this

00:03:15.042 --> 00:03:20.510
goes not all the way but a fair amount of the way to helping us understand this famous problem of evil.

00:03:22.554 --> 00:03:23.535
Where's the evil come from?

00:03:23.575 --> 00:03:25.598
Not all of it, but good deal of it.

00:03:26.780 --> 00:03:27.942
From the abuse of freedom.

00:03:29.404 --> 00:03:34.492
Now think of the billions of people on our planet, all with flawed finite freedoms.

00:03:35.714 --> 00:03:38.618
Will there be conflict and suffering caused by that?

00:03:38.659 --> 00:03:39.580
Of course there will be.

00:03:39.700 --> 00:03:41.803
And you say, why can't God just get rid of this?

00:03:42.244 --> 00:03:43.506
Well, yeah, He could.

00:03:43.682 --> 00:03:45.284
by simply eliminating our freedom.

00:03:46.426 --> 00:03:47.588
How many would sign up for that?

00:03:48.549 --> 00:03:51.814
How many would be willing to say, yeah, Lord, just take away my freedom completely?

00:03:52.475 --> 00:03:54.157
No, no, God doesn't want automatons.

00:03:54.177 --> 00:04:02.930
He wants people that will love him, serve him wittily in the tangle of their minds and love him by real acts of the will.

00:04:03.311 --> 00:04:04.853
See, that's the central point here.

00:04:05.334 --> 00:04:10.561
Now, what triggered this in my mind was the citation now from our first reading from Sirach.

00:04:10.622 --> 00:04:10.962
Listen.

00:04:12.450 --> 00:04:17.156
If you choose, you can keep the commandments and they will save you.

00:04:18.237 --> 00:04:21.501
God has set before you fire and water.

00:04:22.422 --> 00:04:25.766
To whichever you choose, stretch forth your hand.

00:04:26.547 --> 00:04:33.496
Before man, our life and death, good and evil, whichever he chooses shall be given him.

00:04:34.557 --> 00:04:39.183
Now that's simple language, everybody, but it's naming something of supreme importance.

00:04:40.845 --> 00:04:41.746
That's life.

00:04:42.082 --> 00:04:47.529
Like every moment of life, we face this choice.

00:04:49.211 --> 00:04:51.434
Do I walk the path of righteousness or not?

00:04:52.395 --> 00:04:54.898
Do I choose the good or not?

00:04:56.761 --> 00:05:01.647
And you know, whichever he chooses shall be given him, the Lord says, I made you free.

00:05:01.707 --> 00:05:07.374
I'm not here to intervene like a parent that will prevent a child from ever experiencing anything negative.

00:05:07.414 --> 00:05:10.578
No, God gives us this freedom.

00:05:11.202 --> 00:05:13.145
Life and death are before us.

00:05:13.225 --> 00:05:14.847
There's fire and there's water.

00:05:16.390 --> 00:05:18.292
Watch this principle, by the way, throughout the Bible.

00:05:19.114 --> 00:05:23.520
You'll find it in the famous book of Joshua, you know, where he says to the people about to enter the promised land.

00:05:23.700 --> 00:05:28.708
Look, there's the God of Israel and then there's the gods of these people here and it's up to you.

00:05:29.389 --> 00:05:30.571
Which one do you want?

00:05:30.831 --> 00:05:34.797
As for me and my people, we choose the Lord.

00:05:36.299 --> 00:05:41.106
I love that passage because it's behind Bob Dylan's famous, Gotta Serve Somebody.

00:05:41.186 --> 00:05:46.211
When Dylan says, it might be the devil, it might be the Lord, but you're going to have to serve somebody.

00:05:46.591 --> 00:05:47.892
Dead right, by the way.

00:05:48.213 --> 00:05:49.033
It's dead right.

00:05:49.694 --> 00:05:50.715
Oh no, I don't serve anybody.

00:05:51.035 --> 00:05:51.476
Nonsense.

00:05:51.996 --> 00:05:52.917
You serve somebody.

00:05:53.918 --> 00:05:55.139
There's a choice before you.

00:05:55.239 --> 00:05:56.200
It's good or it's evil.

00:05:56.340 --> 00:05:57.421
It's fire or it's water.

00:05:57.962 --> 00:05:59.243
Which path are you going to choose?

00:05:59.663 --> 00:06:03.587
And again, life would be a lot easier in a way if we didn't have these choices.

00:06:04.228 --> 00:06:06.930
But God doesn't want automatons.

00:06:06.990 --> 00:06:08.612
He wants people that will love him.

00:06:09.052 --> 00:06:11.154
And that means free people.

00:06:11.682 --> 00:06:15.707
You know, I might have shared this before with you, but it's a great insight of John Paul II.

00:06:16.668 --> 00:06:19.552
He says, in every act of the will, we're doing two things.

00:06:20.733 --> 00:06:23.837
We're choosing a particular act or particular path.

00:06:23.877 --> 00:06:24.958
You know, do I do this or that?

00:06:25.519 --> 00:06:26.340
So I choose.

00:06:26.940 --> 00:06:34.049
But also implicitly in every choice, I'm choosing the person I'm becoming.

00:06:35.511 --> 00:06:38.194
I'm creating in a way my character.

00:06:38.370 --> 00:06:44.719
As I choose to love rather than to hate, I choose to be charitable rather than to be unkind.

00:06:44.779 --> 00:06:48.944
I choose to walk a positive path rather than a path of resentment.

00:06:49.746 --> 00:07:00.700
Well, I'm doing a particular thing and I'm making myself more virtuous or less virtuous, more godly, less godly.

00:07:00.881 --> 00:07:05.187
My character is also being formed in these acts of the will.

00:07:07.109 --> 00:07:07.730
Well,

00:07:07.906 --> 00:07:16.876
There's the spiritual life in a way and Sirach lays it out to us that every moment of every day we're facing these choices.

00:07:17.877 --> 00:07:19.819
Which one will it be?

00:07:21.641 --> 00:07:22.262
What's heaven?

00:07:23.443 --> 00:07:33.775
Well, we say heaven is the place of perfect love where we answer the love of God with a perfect love of our own.

00:07:34.696 --> 00:07:36.818
So what's this life on this reading?

00:07:36.994 --> 00:07:42.880
This life is a kind of training ground that we need to learn the way of love.

00:07:42.960 --> 00:07:47.104
We need to be formed in the way of love, to be ready for heaven.

00:07:48.105 --> 00:07:58.234
You know, in my dialogues over the years with my Protestant friends and we get into the famous question of, you know, justification by grace through faith alone or through works and all that.

00:07:58.254 --> 00:08:04.100
And, you know, of course, the Catholic teaching is, of course, we're justified by grace through faith.

00:08:04.480 --> 00:08:06.482
You can't be saved apart from that.

00:08:07.266 --> 00:08:18.379
But the church has always said, not by grace and faith alone, but that justification increases and grows precisely through acts of love.

00:08:19.120 --> 00:08:23.364
Because see, in heaven, faith fades away and hope fades away.

00:08:24.205 --> 00:08:26.768
But love remains because love is what heaven is.

00:08:26.828 --> 00:08:35.378
So if you were to arrive in heaven by virtue of your faith, but you had no love, you'd be like a stranger in a strange land.

00:08:36.066 --> 00:08:38.809
You'd be in this realm of love but unable to love.

00:08:39.470 --> 00:08:42.694
And then as Origen, the ancient church father, and C.S.

00:08:42.754 --> 00:08:48.621
Lewis quite rightly saw, the love of God would light up the fires of hell within you.

00:08:48.641 --> 00:08:59.174
See, if you're not suited to divine love, you haven't developed the capacity to respond to the divine love, then God's love will be like a fire to you.

00:08:59.274 --> 00:09:02.738
It'll be like a source of resistance to you.

00:09:03.906 --> 00:09:12.679
And so this life, can we construe it as, you know, a training time, a time when we grow ever more deeply in love?

00:09:13.520 --> 00:09:16.805
Okay, so there's the principle as the Old Testament lays it out.

00:09:17.846 --> 00:09:21.952
Jesus, who said, look, I've come not to abrogate the law, but to fulfill it.

00:09:22.453 --> 00:09:24.276
So he's not saying no to any of that.

00:09:25.137 --> 00:09:28.021
He rather intensifies things.

00:09:29.063 --> 00:09:31.186
If the point is to grow in love, okay,

00:09:32.034 --> 00:09:36.158
then certainly our unloving actions have to be eliminated.

00:09:36.618 --> 00:09:41.103
We have to choose against any acts of hatred, right?

00:09:42.324 --> 00:09:47.389
So the Lord says, certainly you shouldn't kill people.

00:09:48.209 --> 00:09:49.731
That's forbidden in the Ten Commandments.

00:09:50.111 --> 00:09:50.952
That's obviously true.

00:09:50.972 --> 00:09:53.114
If you're killing people, you're not walking the path of love.

00:09:53.735 --> 00:09:54.876
But He intensifies it.

00:09:56.317 --> 00:10:01.362
I say to you, whoever is angry with his brother will be liable to judgment.

00:10:01.506 --> 00:10:05.511
Whoever says, you fool, will be liable to fiery Gehenna.

00:10:06.252 --> 00:10:07.293
Now what's he driving at here?

00:10:09.335 --> 00:10:28.978
If this life is meant to be a training ground of love, that we're meant to cultivate love, yes, evil actions have to be eliminated, but so too must those deep motivations in us that are tainted by hatred, they've got to be eliminated too.

00:10:30.562 --> 00:10:35.549
So, okay, I'm not killing anybody, but I spend a lot of my time angry at people.

00:10:37.632 --> 00:10:39.855
I spend a lot of my time bad-mouthing people.

00:10:40.456 --> 00:10:41.037
You fool.

00:10:42.018 --> 00:10:45.824
How many times in the course of the day ask yourself, everybody, you're all sinners here, right?

00:10:46.385 --> 00:10:51.632
Ask yourself, how often do I cultivate these feelings of resentment and of hatred?

00:10:51.672 --> 00:10:55.417
How often do I share negative assessments of people?

00:10:56.319 --> 00:10:58.642
Well, those aren't loving.

00:10:59.650 --> 00:11:09.923
And so just as I choose against the actions, now listen, I need to choose even against these interior corruptions.

00:11:10.924 --> 00:11:14.629
And you say, well, look, I mean, I can't control my feelings and that's true to a degree.

00:11:16.391 --> 00:11:19.475
But to a degree, you can control them.

00:11:19.495 --> 00:11:26.664
You know, if you have these feelings welling up within you, you can indulge them or you can actively turn from them.

00:11:27.905 --> 00:11:28.466
You can

00:11:28.610 --> 00:11:37.579
You can cultivate them in a perverse way, kind of enjoy them, or you can choose not to do that.

00:11:37.599 --> 00:11:42.084
You can choose to forget them or engage in an act of love or anything else.

00:11:42.944 --> 00:11:45.287
Again, it's a matter of freedom.

00:11:46.108 --> 00:11:52.935
Jesus wants this loving choice to move all the way down.

00:11:54.476 --> 00:11:56.338
And then in a very similar way, listen,

00:11:57.090 --> 00:11:59.253
So you've heard it said, do not commit adultery.

00:11:59.393 --> 00:12:01.075
Okay, that's in the Ten Commandments.

00:12:02.597 --> 00:12:12.310
But I say to you, everyone who looks at a woman with lust has already committed adultery with her in his heart.

00:12:14.572 --> 00:12:19.499
So yes, of course, acts of marital infidelity have to be eliminated.

00:12:19.559 --> 00:12:21.942
Those are not the path of love, obviously.

00:12:23.384 --> 00:12:25.106
But so are

00:12:25.282 --> 00:12:29.607
these sort of lustful, adulterous thoughts that I cultivate.

00:12:30.808 --> 00:12:34.732
Maybe it's not as bad as performing the action, but the actions come from those thoughts.

00:12:35.913 --> 00:12:38.416
Oh, come on, Bishop, I can't control all my thoughts and feelings.

00:12:38.636 --> 00:12:40.158
I know, to some degree, that's true.

00:12:40.599 --> 00:12:43.101
But you can choose not to indulge them.

00:12:43.562 --> 00:12:45.564
You can choose not to cultivate them.

00:12:45.884 --> 00:12:48.247
You can choose not to be preoccupied with them.

00:12:49.949 --> 00:12:51.250
I place before you

00:12:51.394 --> 00:12:53.817
Life and death, fire and water, good and evil.

00:12:54.318 --> 00:12:59.644
Yes, in terms of actions, but also in terms of feelings and motivations.

00:13:01.587 --> 00:13:02.287
What does Jesus say?

00:13:02.307 --> 00:13:08.295
I want you to be perfect as your heavenly Father is perfect.

00:13:08.715 --> 00:13:12.160
So if you say, look on the externals, I got it together.

00:13:12.200 --> 00:13:14.202
I'm not doing these bad things.

00:13:15.143 --> 00:13:18.588
Yeah, but on the inside, remember what he says to the Pharisees?

00:13:18.908 --> 00:13:20.530
Yeah, you're great on the outside.

00:13:21.154 --> 00:13:26.682
But you're like whitewash sepulchres because on the inside you're full of all filth and dead men's bones.

00:13:27.483 --> 00:13:39.301
You see, that's what he's driving at here is my life can look pretty good on the outside, but my motivations and my feelings and my interiority is kind of an unloving mess.

00:13:40.463 --> 00:13:46.772
No, no, let your choice for the good go all the way down.

00:13:47.574 --> 00:13:50.578
You know, God is not interested in spiritual mediocrity.

00:13:51.202 --> 00:13:53.304
Heaven is the place of perfect love.

00:13:54.045 --> 00:13:54.726
It's perfect love.

00:13:55.647 --> 00:13:58.890
Well, this life is a training ground.

00:13:58.931 --> 00:14:00.012
It's a preparation.

00:14:01.774 --> 00:14:02.494
Let's get started.

00:14:03.536 --> 00:14:04.176
Choose the good.

00:14:05.318 --> 00:14:05.938
And God bless you.

00:14:11.184 --> 00:14:14.788
Thank you for listening to this week's homily from Bishop Robert Barron.

00:14:15.168 --> 00:14:20.274
For more resources from Bishop Barron, please visit wordonfire.org.
